    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-06-17T18:22:14Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Miranda Vargas School Bus Driver Red Flag Act or Miranda's Law</strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration to issue a final rule requiring the implementation of a national employer notification service that states may access. The term &quot;employer notification service&quot; means a service that automatically provides a report to an employer (with notice to the employee involved) on the change in the status of the driving record or license of an employee who has a commercial driver's license due to a conviction, license suspension or revocation, or any other action taken against the driving privilege.</p> <p><br> </p>]]></text>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
